  "texts": [
    "We invited these participants specifically, because they completed the Big Five personality test (i.e., the 30-item BFI-2-S) 57 in our earlier experiments.",
    "This allowed us to extract their personality profiles ahead of the current study to prompt ChatGPT to create personality-tailored ads unique to each participant.",
    "The overall procedure for this study was as follows.",
    "First, we calculated the percentile scores for Openness, Extraversion and Conscientiousness for each participant (based on the means and standard deviations of all participants from Studies 1-3).",
    "We again did not consider Neuroticism (i.e., due to its unique theoretical nature), and likewise, did not include Agreeableness as our previous studies suggested no significant matching-effects for this trait (see \"Discussion\")."
  ],
